# Read by @expo/fingerprint (runtimeVersion policy "fingerprint").
#
# Why: EAS build workers recompute the fingerprint DURING the build, and their
# node_modules copies of the RN-core-autolinked libraries no longer hash the
# same as the trigger environment's pristine `npm ci` (worker-side mutation
# around pod install / codegen). Every such build then dies with
# "Runtime version calculated on local machine not equal to runtime version
# calculated during build", diffing exactly these dir sources.
#
# Ignoring the DIR CONTENTS is safe: each library's resolved version still
# lands in the fingerprint via the rncoreAutolinkingConfig JSON source, so
# upgrading any of these packages still changes the runtime and forces a new
# dev build. What is lost is content-level detection of in-place edits to
# these node_modules dirs (e.g. patch-package) — this repo has none; if
# patches are ever added, remove the affected line here.
node_modules/@react-native-async-storage/async-storage/**/*
node_modules/expo/**/*
node_modules/react-native-gesture-handler/**/*
node_modules/react-native-get-random-values/**/*
node_modules/react-native-reanimated/**/*
node_modules/react-native-safe-area-context/**/*
node_modules/react-native-screens/**/*
node_modules/react-native-svg/**/*
node_modules/react-native-view-shot/**/*
node_modules/react-native-worklets/**/*
